# GitHub Configuration

This directory contains GitHub-specific configuration files for the Taran repository.

## Files

### `settings.yml`
Automated repository configuration file used by the [GitHub Settings App](https://github.com/apps/settings).

**Purpose**: Automatically applies repository settings including branch protection rules.

**Setup**: 
1. Install the [GitHub Settings App](https://github.com/apps/settings) on the repository
2. The app will automatically apply the settings defined in this file

**Key Features**:
- Protects the `main` branch from direct pushes
- Requires pull request reviews before merging
- Enforces code quality standards

### `CODEOWNERS`
Defines code ownership and automatic review requests.

**Purpose**: Automatically requests reviews from designated owners when PRs are opened.

**How it works**: When a pull request modifies files, GitHub automatically requests reviews from the owners defined in this file.

### `BRANCH_PROTECTION.md`
Documentation explaining the branch protection policy and workflow.

**Purpose**: Provides guidance for contributors on how to work with protected branches.

## Branch Protection

The `main` branch is protected to ensure:
- No direct pushes
- All changes go through pull requests
- Code review is mandatory
- Quality standards are maintained

See [BRANCH_PROTECTION.md](BRANCH_PROTECTION.md) for detailed information.
